{"type":"message","id":"952676dc","parentId":"b606b19a","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:28:13.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context.json shows that the bootstrap hook ran (timestamp is from when this session started at 21:27), but the session-summary content was NOT injected - it only has the basic classification/scoring fields from the gateway's initial processing.\n\nThe session-summary files that should have been created don't exist in the memory directory. The hook chain is:\n1. ephemeral captures messages ✅ (messages are being captured)\n2. session-summary hook generates a summary ✅ (but there's no session-summary file)\n3. bootstrap hook reads the summary and injects it ✅ (but there's no summary to read)\n\nWait, looking at the context.json more carefully - this session started at 21:27. The classification scene is \"clarify\" and confidence is 0.598. \n\nThe scoring came back at 0, which is odd. I'm not finding any session-summary files in the memory directory, so either the hook didn't trigger or it failed silently. Looking at the pipeline - ephemeral captured this message, but session-summary didn't create a file, which means bootstrap had nothing to inject. The system messages I see are the SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md content that came through in the system prompt, not from the hooks themselves.\n\nSo the issue is clear: ephemeral is working, but the downstream steps aren't firing. The auto-score-classify hook should be calling 3105 to classify and score the message, then session-summary should create a file from that. I need to figure out whether the problem is in the auto-score-classify hook or if it's not being triggered at all. The real issue is that ephemeral captures messages, then session-summary generates a summary file, and bootstrap is supposed to inject that file into new sessions—but that last step isn't happening. I need to verify whether session-summary is actually creating those files and whether the bootstrap hook is properly configured to read them when a new session starts. The ephemeral hook captured messages but never triggered session-summary to create a summary file, so there's nothing for bootstrap to inject. The classification/scoring data in context.json came from the gateway's built-in 3104 classifier, not from the custom hooks I set up. This points to either the hooks not being properly registered or the session-summary hook never firing to generate the summary files that bootstrap needs. in session-summary, which then generates the summary file. But if the session-summary hook isn't firing—either because it's not properly registered or because the trigger conditions aren't met—then no summary file gets created, and bootstrap has nothing to inject.\n\nI should check whether the hooks are actually registered and firing, and look at the session-summary configuration to understand why it's not creating summary files even though ephemeral messages are being captured.","thinkingSignature":"865d2d06bf9e631465292576930435d58801d92db264fc4d104c0eaaa5374967"},{"type":"text","text":"还没完全跑通。ephemeral 有数据，但 session-summary 文件没生成（也就没有可注入的内容）。bootstrap hook 的逻辑之前修过，但 session-summary hook 的触发时机有问题——消息被捕获了，却没有触发摘要生成。\n\n来快速验证一下当前钩子状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5a8rx782gj5g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw hooks list 2>/dev/null || cat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('hooks', d.get('plugins', {})), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4066,"output":691,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24507,"cost":{"input":0.0012198,"output":0.0008292,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003234}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173272584,"responseId":"062d73d84c8aa45c585208c4d213a830"}}
