{"type":"message","id":"46158612","parentId":"47efebd7","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:20.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me also check if there's a summary file for today in the memory directory that I might have missed.\n\nThe issue is:1. ephemeral captured messages ✅2. But session-summary hook didn't create a file ❌3. Therefore bootstrap hook couldn't inject anything\n\nLet me check the bootstrap hook to see what it was supposed to inject.","thinkingSignature":"b75b80979d44d8f8717f0bebff6a402207748062ff228eb3ce331600028596d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wuip484yhm0a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/context-hook.js 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10213,"output":117,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30080,"cost":{"input":0.0030639,"output":0.0001404,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0043893000000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173356410,"responseId":"062d742bd84a5f9f546b096485a0705d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fba6a645","parentId":"46158612","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:20.780Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wuip484yhm0a_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 保护层未加载，跳过');\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理用户消息\n    if (event.type === 'message' || event.type === 'message:receive') {\n      const content = event.message?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('user', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] 用户消息已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 处理 Agent 回复\n    if (event.type === 'message:send' || event.type === 'agent:response') {\n      const content = event.response?.content || event.content || '';\n      if (content) {\n        global.openclaw?.addContextMessage('assistant', content, event.taskId);\n        console.log('[ContextHook] AI回复已记录:', content.slice(0, 30));\n      }\n    }\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[ContextHook] 错误:', error.message);\n  }\n};\n\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776173360769}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb0ecefe","parentId":"fba6a645","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:25.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a different context-hook.js, not the bootstrap hook. Let me check the memory-bootstrap skill's handler.","thinkingSignature":"e31344bb4414e87360f9cfdd319bfdd82b60f8f630beed99d8f40b00368f5b52"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mtmwj9gqykak_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/skills/memory-bootstrap/hooks/openclaw/handler.js 2>/dev/null | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10713,"output":73,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30536,"cost":{"input":0.0032139,"output":0.0000876,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0044865}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173360781,"responseId":"062d7430b5994ba3e99a8ff7ed5ab2a0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"56297d56","parentId":"eb0ecefe","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:25.233Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mtmwj9gqykak_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Memory Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n * Injects MEMORY.md + recent session summaries as virtual bootstrap files.\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') return;\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') return;\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') return;\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) return;\n\n  const workspaceDir = event.context.workspaceDir || process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR;\n  if (!workspaceDir) return;\n\n  const memoryRoot = `${workspaceDir}/memory`;\n  const memoryMdPath = `${workspaceDir}/MEMORY.md`;\n\n  // Read MEMORY.md (long-term memory index)\n  try {\n    const { readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const memoryContent = await readFile(memoryMdPath, 'utf-8').catch(() => null);\n    if (memoryContent) {\n      event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n        path: 'MEMORY.md',\n        content: memoryContent.slice(0, 2000),\n        virtual: true,\n      });\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip */ }\n\n  // Read recent session summaries from memory/\n  try {\n    const { readdir, readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const files = await readdir(memoryRoot);\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n      .sort()\n      .reverse()\n      .slice(0, 3);\n\n    for (const file of summaryFiles) {\n      try {\n        const content = await readFile(`${memoryRoot}/${file}`, 'utf-8');\n        if (content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->') && content.length < 2000) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content,\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        } else if (!content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->')) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content: content.slice(0, 1000),\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip individual file errors */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip directory errors */ }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":60,"aggregated":"/**\n * Memory Bootstrap Hook for OpenClaw\n *\n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n * Injects MEMORY.md + recent session summaries as virtual bootstrap files.\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  // Safety checks for event structure\n  if (!event || typeof event !== 'object') return;\n  if (event.type !== 'agent' || event.action !== 'bootstrap') return;\n  if (!event.context || typeof event.context !== 'object') return;\n  if (!Array.isArray(event.context.bootstrapFiles)) return;\n\n  const workspaceDir = event.context.workspaceDir || process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR;\n  if (!workspaceDir) return;\n\n  const memoryRoot = `${workspaceDir}/memory`;\n  const memoryMdPath = `${workspaceDir}/MEMORY.md`;\n\n  // Read MEMORY.md (long-term memory index)\n  try {\n    const { readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const memoryContent = await readFile(memoryMdPath, 'utf-8').catch(() => null);\n    if (memoryContent) {\n      event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n        path: 'MEMORY.md',\n        content: memoryContent.slice(0, 2000),\n        virtual: true,\n      });\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip */ }\n\n  // Read recent session summaries from memory/\n  try {\n    const { readdir, readFile } = await import('node:fs/promises');\n    const files = await readdir(memoryRoot);\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n      .sort()\n      .reverse()\n      .slice(0, 3);\n\n    for (const file of summaryFiles) {\n      try {\n        const content = await readFile(`${memoryRoot}/${file}`, 'utf-8');\n        if (content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->') && content.length < 2000) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content,\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        } else if (!content.includes('<!-- summary-only -->')) {\n          event.context.bootstrapFiles.push({\n            path: `memory/${file}`,\n            content: content.slice(0, 1000),\n            virtual: true,\n          });\n        }\n      } catch { /* skip individual file errors */ }\n    }\n  } catch { /* skip directory errors */ }\n};\n\nexport default handler;\nmodule.exports = handler;\nmodule.exports.default = handler;","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776173365220}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f939cd9","parentId":"56297d56","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:34.766Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The bootstrap hook:\n1. Reads MEMORY.md ✅ (it was injected as part of the system prompt in Project Context)\n2. Reads recent session summaries from memory/ - but there are NO session-summary files!So the bootstrap hook is working correctly - it just has nothing to inject because there are no session-summary files.The problem is that the session-summary hook is enabled but not creating files. Let me check why.\n\nLooking at the session-summary handler again, it's triggered on `/new` or `/reset`. But it's NOT creating a file. Let me check what `resolveSessionFile` returns for webchat sessions - it mentions that webchat sessions have no .jsonl files, so it falls back to searching the agents/main/sessions/ directory.\n\n\nThe hook fired on /new but couldn't find the previous session file, so it probably wrote a summary anyway using just the ephemeral data. But I'm not seeing any session-summary files in the memory directory, so I need to check the workspace configuration to see where files are actually being written.","thinkingSignature":"cbbc89eb25c590e4fc8b21430638e4d0ad1a5be4564d5817cb01221a4504cf3b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hh04lo4jm56d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"WORKSPACE_DIR: $OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR\"; cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('workspaceDir:', d.get('workspace', d.get('workspaceDir', 'not found')))\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hh04lo4jm56d_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11358,"output":341,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31449,"cost":{"input":0.0034073999999999997,"output":0.0