{"type":"message","id":"d116c0b9","parentId":"a2eaf0de","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:29:40.160Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. The `memory` directory is at `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/`, not at `~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/`. The workspace for the main agent is `main`, but the shared memory directory is at `memory` (without `main`).So the session-summary hook writes to `MEMORY_DIR` which resolves to `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/` (since `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR` is not set, it uses the default).Let me check if there are any session-summary files in the actual memory directory.","thinkingSignature":"d7c0dbd52262a4f1fee5359dd3cedfb9ce15591a2f9bf6381e919c84419b5a35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dqdzz65chwpz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ | grep -i summary 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11956,"output":165,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31871,"cost":{"input":0.0035868,"output":0.000198,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0049698}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173374911,"responseId":"062d743e476db6743750ae65de4c737f"}}
