{"type":"message","id":"43e3d5e7","parentId":"812837bd","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:30:04.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see. The session-summary from Apr 13 confirms that the session-summary hook is supposed to create files. But for today (Apr 14), there should be a new session-summary file that was created when /new was called at 21:27.\n\nLet me check again if there's a session-summary file from today. Earlier I only found the Apr 13 one.\n\nThe issue might be that the session-summary hook ran but the summary was written to the wrong directory. Or it failed to run.\n\nLet me check what session key the current session uses and what the hook's logic does for webchat sessions.\n\nActually, let me just directly check what files exist that were created today after 21:27.","thinkingSignature":"7166c27af052172012009d8077e9e7541bfd16d6b5f0b78761419dbbfc448053"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f1tti9qs55ph_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw/workspace -name \"*-session-summary.md\" -newer ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/2026-04-14.md 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f1tti9qs55ph_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*-session-summary.md\" -newer ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/2026-04-14.md 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13865,"output":261,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33876,"cost":{"input":0.0041595,"output":0.00031319999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0056577}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173396949,"responseId":"062d7454f415afe2221a553986a3a95a"}}
