{"type":"message","id":"1426a286","parentId":"cf7d6630","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:32:27.130Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway logs go to a socket (probably a logging service) rather than a file. Let me try a different approach - trigger a new /new session and watch for hook activity in real time, or just manually check what the session-summary hook would produce given the current session data.\n\nActually, let me just look at the session data directly to understand what's happening. The latest session is `e6b3bbe2-7c8b-41d8-8a5d-38ac0dae4b63.jsonl`. This is the current webchat session. Let me check its content.\n\nActually, let me try to trigger a manual hook run to see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"748b8a70a816ecfd3c7d3aa94556d847d190c26ed61f59173f5c4554e6ba3546"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oopesuhqh314_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/e6b3bbe2-7c8b-41d8-8a5d-38ac0dae4b63.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nlines = sys.stdin.read().strip().split('\\n')\nprint(f'Total entries: {len(lines)}')\nfor l in lines[-5:]:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(l)\n        t = d.get('type','?')\n        r = d.get('message',{}).get('role','?') if isinstance(d.get('message'),dict) else '?'\n        c = str(d.get('message',{}).get('content',''))[:80] if isinstance(d.get('message'),dict) else str(d).get('content','')[:80]\n        print(f'{t} | {r} | {c}')\n    except: print(l[:100])\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15367,"output":362,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35479,"cost":{"input":0.0046101,"output":0.0004344,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.006229499999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173537286,"responseId":"062d74e1390347235317fdbd10478a05"}}
