{"type":"message","id":"dcf07a28","parentId":"430754d1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:32:35.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the session jsonl has the current conversation. This is the ACTIVE session file, not the previous one. The session-summary hook needs the previous session file. Let me look at the session files more carefully.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the gateway process logs are going to the openclaw-gateway process's stdout (socket), and there's no file log. Let me try to check the gateway config for logging settings, or try to see if there's a way to get the gateway logs.\n\nLet me look at the config to see if there's a log file path configured.","thinkingSignature":"5ac9274be50ca46ad6e8e68eb92e437fe747cce280e1f0f2452c2fd3d1ff93a9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w7ffg22zvydx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); gw=d.get('gateway',{}); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in gw.items() if 'log' in k.lower()}, indent=2))\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w7ffg22zvydx_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.log\" -newer ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/2026-04-14.md 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15872,"output":258,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35880,"cost":{"input":0.0047615999999999995,"output":0.0003096,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0062562}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173547217,"responseId":"062d74eb0a0d64cd0e9c378c1afb0a8f"}}
