{"type":"message","id":"a66713f3","parentId":"5f2e5d9f","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:32:47.672Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No gateway log file configured. The gateway logs go to stdout which is captured by systemd. Since journalctl has no entries for openclaw, the gateway must be running as a background process without systemd. Let me try to get the gateway logs another way.\n\nActually, let me just try to look at the session-summary hook context to understand what data it would have received during the /new at 21:27. The hook fires on agent:bootstrap, and the context should have session info.\n\nLet me try a different approach - manually emit a hook event to see what happens. Or better, let me look at what event.context looks like by checking if there's a way to inspect the bootstrap event.\n \nThe real issue is that session-summary didn't generate a summary file. When the /new happened at 21:27, the hook should've fired and created one, but it didn't. Let me check the workspace config to see where MEMORY_DIR actually points to in the hook's logic.\n\nLooking at the hook code, MEMORY_DIR resolves to `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/`, and I can see there is a 2026-04-13-session-summary.md file there. But the hook ran at 21:27 today, so it should've generated a new summary file for the current session that doesn't exist yet.\n\nLet me trace through the hook's execution path to figure out where it's failing.","thinkingSignature":"db7c8ca766afa57661109845a592c116b2195c11d0537d4d942e76d024d6760b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nzrzsqx9ulpz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js 2>/dev/null | grep -n \"run\\|export\\|module\" | tail -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nzrzsqx9ulpz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Simulate what the hook would produce for the current session by checking the latest jsonl\nLATEST=$(ls -t ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/*