{"type":"message","id":"8b78408c","parentId":"10a08b6b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:33:09.778Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the picture clearly:\n\nAt 21:27 (13:26 UTC), `/new` was triggered:\n1. Session `b1c0599e-6334-4331-b126-fbb89c588c9f.jsonl` (current at 21:25) was renamed to `b1c0599e-6334-4331-b126-fbb89c588c9f.jsonl.reset.2026-04-14T13-26-09.707Z`\n2. A new session `e6b3bbe2-7c8b-41d8-8a5d-38ac0dae4b63.jsonl` started\n\n\n3. When the session-summary hook fired, it had `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile = \"/path/to/b1c0599e...jsonl.reset.2026-04-14T13-26-09.707Z\"`, but the hook's `resolveSessionFile` function was looking for the current session file, not the reset one, so it likely failed to locate the previous session's data.\n\nThe function checks if `currentSessionFile` contains `.reset.` and returns it directly if it does, which seems right in theory. But looking at the actual code structure, `previousSessionEntry.sessionFile` gets passed as `currentSessionFile` to `findPreviousSessionFile`, and the logic appears to be searching for the active file before the reset happened, not the reset file itself.\n\nThe issue is that after the reset, `b1c0599e-...reset.2026-04-14T13-26-09.707Z` should be found directly since it contains `.reset.`, but I need to trace through whether `base` extraction is stripping that part incorrectly or if the fallback logic is kicking in when it shouldn't be. The issue is that `path.basename()` returns the full filename including the `.reset.` timestamp suffix, so when the code tries to strip it with `.replace(/\\.reset\\..+$/, '')`, it doesn't match the format and returns the entire basename unchanged. Then when checking if that unmodified basename exists in the fileSet, it fails because the actual files have the full reset suffix. I'm realizing the core issue: `workspaceDir` is undefined since `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR` isn't set, so `sessionsDir` defaults to the home directory path, but the `sessionId` from `previousSessionEntry` appears to be missing or empty, which breaks the lookup entirely.","thinkingSignature":"6ad4d4efceef4f692cd06c574e17811e8d2f0dc998558b2691e854d9bf27e4c1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r2qlx0kexrs1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js 2>/dev/null | grep -n \"workspaceDir\\|WORKSPACE\\|OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17916,"output":586,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38252,"cost":{"input":0.0053748,"output":0.0007032,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007263}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173573844,"responseId":"062d7505bf133a40c12adc392695b3df"}}
