{"type":"message","id":"215407b6","parentId":"93cfa488","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:33:23.129Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context.json only has classification, scoring, timestamp, and messagePreview. It doesn't have workspaceDir or session info. This is a lightweight context file used by the v8 scorer/classifier, not the full bootstrap context.\n\nSo the session-summary hook context doesn't have workspaceDir, which means sessionsDir falls back to `$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions` which is correct.\n\nThe issue must be in the session file resolution. Let me look at the actual previous session file path more carefully.\n\nPrevious session at /new time (21:27): `b1c0599e-6334-4331-b126-fbb89c588c9f.jsonl.reset.2026-04-14T13-26-09.707Z`\n\n\nNow I'm checking the sessionId values from the reset file and the previous session ID to see if there's a mismatch between what the hook is receiving and what's actually stored.","thinkingSignature":"c946844095752c5439b6c68addd7455681cf59d1240f9603c4800c990cdd6bde"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6v0ex66q8d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -1 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/b1c0599e-6334-4331-b126-fbb89c588c9f.jsonl.reset.2026-04-14T13-26-09.707Z 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.loads(sys.stdin.read()); print('sessionId:', d.get('sessionId','?')); print('type:', d.get('type','?'))\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iz6v0ex66q8d_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -3 ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/e6b3bbe2-7c8b-41d8-8a5d-38ac0dae4b63.jsonl 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nfor l in sys.stdin.read().strip().split('\\n')[:3]:\n    try:\n        d=json.loads(l)\n        print('type:', d.get('type'), '| sessionId:', d.get('sessionId', d.get('session_id','?'))[:50])\n    except: pass\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18996,"output":452,"cacheRead":197