{"type":"message","id":"31138dc5","parentId":"f580b225","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:34:39.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There IS a session summary file from 13:26 (21:26 CST)! The file is named `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md` because the slug generation from the fallback summary produced \"无会话内容\".\n\nSo the session-summary hook DID run and DID write a file. The previous session had essentially no meaningful content (just the /new trigger), so it generated a fallback \"无会话内容\" summary.\n\nNow the question is: why didn't the bootstrap hook inject this file? Let me check the bootstrap hook's filtering logic.\n\nThe bootstrap hook looks for files with `<!-- summary-only -->` that are less than 2000 characters AND files without that tag. \n\nLooking at the bootstrap hook code, it filters for files matching a date pattern or containing \"summary\" in the name, excluding MEMORY files, then sorts them in reverse order and takes the top 3.\n\nFor each candidate file, it checks whether it contains the `<!-- summary-only -->` marker—if it does and is under 2000 characters, or if it doesn't have that marker at all, the content gets included (capped at 1000 characters for non-summary files).\n\nThe file I found has that summary-only tag and is only 213 characters, so it should definitely be picked up. But the bootstrap hook is supposed to fire before the workspace files are injected, which means it runs during the bootstrap phase, not after. That's the real issue here.\n\nLooking at the handler code, it's listening for an `agent:bootstrap` event with `action: 'bootstrap'`, and when that fires, it adds the bootstrap files to the context. But the question is whether this hook is actually being triggered at the right time in the session initialization process. the session. So the hook might not be firing at all, or it's firing but not at the right time to inject context into the new session. The bootstrap context might already be baked in before the hook can modify it.\n\nLet me think through this differently. If `event.context.workspaceDir` is undefined, the `sessionsDir` would fall back to the home directory, which means it would be looking in the wrong place for session files. That could explain why the hook isn't working as expected - it's searching in the wrong directory entirely.\n\nActually, wait. The workspace is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main`, so `event.context.workspaceDir` should point there. That means `sessionsDir` would correctly resolve to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/agents/main/sessions`. But in that directory, the session files might not exist or might be structured differently than the hook expects.\n\nThe real issue is that the bootstrap hook is looking for session files using the session key as a filename, but the actual sessions are stored in a JSON file, not as individual session directories. So the hook can't find what it's looking for.\n\nEven if the hook fails to inject session summaries, it should still be loading MEMORY.md since that file is explicitly checked in the bootstrap code. But the user is saying the context pipeline isn't working, so something's still broken. Let me trace through the actual file being generated and why it's not making it into the bootstrap context.\n\nThe session summary file that was created has the summary-only tag and is only 213 characters, well under the 2000 character limit. When the bootstrap hook runs, it sorts all summary files in reverse order and takes the top 3, so this file should definitely be included in the bootstrap files array that gets passed to the LLM.\n\nThe issue might be that `event.context.bootstrapFiles` isn't actually being used by the gateway, or the gateway is overriding the injected bootstrap files with its own context loading mechanism instead.\n\nLet me check the gateway startup logs to see if the agent bootstrapped successfully and what context it actually received.","thinkingSignature":"ef60135d1d3edbcaebfffeaed3331c28a7eacbd5d9e798ed2f18b974a83f4c9b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qss045bhtthp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('gateway',{}), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22872,"output":860,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43482,"cost":{"input":0.0068616,"output":0.001032,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009078600000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173653355,"responseId":"062d75559f17b01deb0b3ef0a23d94ae"}}
