{"type":"message","id":"c9959057","parentId":"99e706d3","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:34:47.911Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No log configuration in the gateway. The gateway logs go to stdout which is either captured by systemd or just lost. Since the gateway was started without systemd (it's running as a user process), its stdout goes to a pipe or is lost.\n\nLet me try a different approach - trigger the hook manually to see what happens. Actually, let me just check the actual bootstrap flow by looking at the gateway's behavior. Maybe there's an issue with how the bootstrapFiles are injected.\n\nActually, let me re-read the bootstrap hook handler more carefully. There's an issue: the hook imports `path` but `path` is a Node.js built-in. The hook uses `process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR`, but there's also a `workspaceDir` passed as parameter from the `run` function.\n \nI need to trace through what `workspaceDir` actually contains when the hook runs during the `/new` session startup.","thinkingSignature":"742a59d504932db4d261f7a37da15c9bba4a1df90197a106c8eaa86c386db47b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q3reclbmn61f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/handler.js 2>/dev/null | grep -n \"workspaceDir\\|event.context\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23863,"output":242,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43855,"cost":{"input":0.007158899999999999,"output":0.0002904,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0086343}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173679828,"responseId":"062d75706c27484fc689ec121eab71fb"}}
