{"type":"message","id":"f055dcfa","parentId":"d7ac3f07","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:34:54.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `workspaceDir` is derived from `event.context.workspaceDir`, with a fallback to `$HOME/.openclaw/workspace` if `event.context.cfg` exists.\n\nFor the webchat `agent:main:main` session, `event.context.workspaceDir` would be the workspace of the main session, which is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main`.\n\nSo `sessionsDir` = `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main/agents/main/sessions`.\n\nBut the actual session files are in `/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`, not in the workspace subdirectory!\n\n\nThis is a path mismatch—the hook is looking in the wrong directory entirely. Yet somehow it found the reset file, which suggests either the workspace has a symlink to the actual sessions directory, or the file path resolution is working differently than I thought. Let me check if there's actually a symlink there.","thinkingSignature":"73fc5049bbacb9600b501d9daf891037bcb709179e437ff47bcfffdd5bc29ef2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dueh85q602is_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/agents/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No agents dir in workspace\"\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24240,"output":256,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44246,"cost":{"input":0.007272,"output":0.0003072,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0087642}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776173688033,"responseId":"062d75777704e2a473a8c1daed2a64bb"}}
