{"type":"message","id":"049ab690","parentId":"dfb855f8","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:36:04.851Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the session-summary hook wrote the fallback \"无会话内容\" summary at 13:26 UTC (21:26 CST) for `agent:main:main`. The previous session was very short (just contained the /new trigger message and startup sequence).\n\nNow, the bootstrap hook should fire at the NEXT /new (which was at 21:27 CST). But wait - the current session we're in started at 21:27. At that /new time, the PREVIOUS session was `b1c0599e...` which was the session from ~21:25-21:26 (just the startup sequence, essentially empty).\n \nThe hook ran and generated a fallback summary for that empty session, but here's the problem: when I injected the bootstrap files into the current session, I included this \"无会话内容\" summary from the previous session, which is just the /new trigger with no actual content.\n\nThe real issue is that the session-summary hook is firing on `agent:bootstrap` AFTER the session starts, which means it's summarizing the previous session's empty content rather than capturing what actually happened before the reset. I need to figure out where this hook is supposed to be triggering from in the gateway.\n\nLet me check the actual gateway configuration to see what events are registered and why the session-summary file might not be showing up as a bootstrap file. I should also look at what the bootstrap handler is doing with the session-summary file - it checks for files containing \"summary\" or matching a date pattern, filters out the MEMORY file, sorts them in reverse chronological order, and takes the top few to inject into the context.\n\nThe bootstrap hook loads these files as virtual entries with a path like `memory/YYYY-MM-DD-*.md` and a content preview of around 1000 characters. But I'm realizing there's a discrepancy between what SOUL.md specifies (which says to read from `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` for recent context) and what the bootstrap hook is actually doing with the session-summary files - they might be getting filtered or injected differently than expected.\n\nLooking at the filter criteria more carefully, the \"无会话内容\" summary file contains `<!-- summary-only -->`, is only 213 characters (well under the 2000 character limit), and matches the date pattern, so it should pass through. The real question is whether this file is actually being loaded as the session context when it should be, or if there's a timing issue with when the bootstrap hook runs relative to when the session context is needed.","thinkingSignature":"a4c14af98379d0c2cc63575fcbd50a288c7a8535e995089a834fac1c457cbd14"},{"type":"text","text":"好消息：session-summary hook **其实跑了**，并且写了文件。\n\n[[reply_to_current]]\n\n找到了关键证据——`memory/2026-04-14-无会话内容.md`，时间戳 21:26，内容是 fallback 摘要\"无会话内容\"。\n\n**链路现状**：\n\n| 环节 | 状态 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|\n| /new 触发 | ✅ | 21:26 和 21:27 各触发一次 |\n| session-summary hook 执行 | ✅ | 写了 fallback 摘要（因为上个小session只有启动序列） |\n| session-summary 文件生成 | ✅ | `2026-04-14-无会话内容.md` 已存在 |\n| bootstrap hook 注入 | ⚠️ | 逻辑正确，但无法直接确认是否送到 LLM |\n| bootstrapFiles → LLM | ⚠️ | **这里可能是断点**——gateway 是否真的把 bootstrapFiles 注入进去了？ |\n\n**真正的问题**：上次 /new 时，前一个 session 只有启动序列（/new 触发 → 回答\"请先读 SOUL.md...\"），没有实际对话内容，所以摘要就是空的。\n\n要不要我手动触发一次 /new，然后立刻检查 bootstrap 是否真的注入了 session-summary？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26819,"output":768,"cacheRead":19750,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47337,"cost":{"input":0.0080457,"output":0.0009216,"cacheRead":0.0011849999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0101523}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776173737411,"responseId":"062d75a90f653156182806121bfbba84"}}
